value.title: FLASHBACK, October 2001: Joe Biden Says Afghanistan War Will Not "Become A Swamp" Like Vietnam
value.excerpt: NBC's Steve Kornacki unearthed footage of then-Senator Joe Biden speaking in favor of the October 2001 invasion of Afghanistan during an interview with Chris Matthews, arguing why it will not become a long-term "swamp" commitment like the Vietnam War.

value.title: Biden warns ISIS-K: ‘We are not done with you yet’
value.excerpt: In a defiant speech Tuesday, President Biden stood by his decision to withdraw all troops from Afghanistan but warned the terrorist group ISIS-K, “We are not done with you yet.”

value.title: Cruz, Roy slam Biden admin over 'man-made' border crisis as fentanyl deaths skyrocket
value.excerpt: The Republican lawmakers are traveling around Texas to learn more from local officials and stakeholders about how the border crisis is affecting them.

value.title: Biden officials 'working around the clock' to 'vet all Afghans' before entry into US
value.excerpt: The White House said Tuesday that intelligence and counterterrorism officials are “working around the clock” to “vet all Afghans” before allowing them to enter the United States, after safely evacuating them from Kabul in recent weeks.

value.title: Donald Trump is not a ‘big fan’ of crypto
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump lashed out at cryptocurrencies in an interview with Fox News on Tuesday. “I have not been a big fan of cryptos,” Trump told Fox. While the interview focused primarily on Trump’s reaction to America’s Afghanistan exit,

value.title: CNN analyst slammed for blaming Trump for collapsed Republican trust in national media: 'Simply breathtaking'
value.excerpt: CNN analyst and New Yorker writer Susan Glasser blamed former President Donald Trump's rhetoric for the plummet in GOP trust in national media over the past five years.

value.title: Pete Hegseth rips Biden for checking watch, calls out 'betrayal' of US military mission
value.excerpt: Army veteran and ‘Fox & Friends Weekend’ co-host Pete Hegseth ripped into Joe Biden on Monday after Gold Star families criticized the president for repeatedly checking his watch while meeting with them.

value.title: Ingraham: Team Biden 'building back weaker' with officials on 'summer break'
value.excerpt: Laura Ingraham said Biden is "building back weaker" Monday on "The Ingraham Angle," noting the "heart-wrenching" situation in Afghanistan as the remainder of U.S. troops left the country.

value.title: Fathers of Marines killed in Kabul blast rip Biden: 'He talked more about his son than my son'
value.excerpt: Two Gold Star fathers of U.S. Marines killed in an ISIS-K-linked blast in Kabul amid President Joe Biden's Afghanistan withdrawal process lambasted the Delaware Democrat for acting selfish in their interactions on "Hannity.

value.title: ‘Disgraceful’, ‘shameful’: Republican outrage after Biden ends pullout
value.excerpt: Congressional Republicans were livid after the Biden administration announced that the evacuation of Americans from Afghanistan had ended.

value.title: Biden Education Department opens civil rights investigations into 5 states for banning school mask mandates
value.excerpt: The U.S. Department of Education is opening an investigation into whether prohibitions on indoor masking mandates constitute discrimination against kids with disabilities.

value.title: Trump big tech suit lawyer predicts case headed to Supreme Court, says gov't pressure made firms state actors
value.excerpt: John Coale leads former President Donald Trump's lawsuit against big tech companies Facebook, Twitter and YouTube, which is owned by Google.

value.title: Naomi Biden seen in chic dress at friend’s wedding in Italy
value.excerpt: Naomi Biden was seen partying in style and luxury with her boyfriend at her side during a friend’s wedding in Como, Italy.

value.title: Jake Sullivan: Biden 'will stop at nothing' to get justice for fallen service members after ISIS-K attack
value.excerpt: National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan said that President Biden will ensure that the U.S. exacts retribution against the terror group known as ISIS-K following a deadly suicide bombing at Afghanistan's Hamid Karzai International Airport in Kabul, while noting that there remains a risk of more attacks.

value.title: Who is Deanne Criswell, Biden’s FEMA boss?
value.excerpt: As Louisiana and the Gulf Coast braced for Hurricane Ida, set to make landfall on Sunday potentially as a Category 4 storm, the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) was expected to play a key role in disaster relief.

value.title: Al Sharpton to Biden: Black community is being stabbed ‘in the back’
value.excerpt: Rev. Al Sharpton hit the stage Saturday during a voting rights rally to tell President Biden that supporters of the filibuster are “stabbing” the Black community “in the back.”

value.title: DeSantis requests Biden administration stop resettling illegal immigrants in Florida
value.excerpt: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis this week wrote to the Biden administration, asking it to stop resettling illegal immigrants in the state of Florida -- and to either deport them instead, or send them to a state that supports the "flouting of our immigration laws."

value.title: Joe Biden just ruined America’s ‘special relationship’ with Great Britain
value.excerpt: Despite such loud promises that he would make America’s alliances great again, Biden’s initially foolish, now fatal, Afghan catastrophe has atomized US international ties.

value.title: Biden meets with Israeli prime minister after deadly Kabul bombing
value.excerpt: President Biden sat down with the newly installed Israeli Prime Minister Naftali Bennett Friday, roughly 24 hours after the deadly suicide bombing in Kabul.

value.title: Elliott Abrams: I'm afraid people will pay for Biden's 'stubbornness' with their lives
value.excerpt: Former deputy national security adviser Elliott Abrams blasted President Biden for his "stubbornness" that could cost human lives.

value.title: Trump says Kabul airport explosion wouldn’t have happened if he was president
value.excerpt: Donald Trump hammered Biden over the suicide bombings outside Kabul’s airport, claiming that “it would not have happened if I was your president.”

value.title: Psaki dismisses calls for Biden to resign: 'Not a day for politics'
value.excerpt: White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki dismissed calls for President Joe Biden to resign in the wake of a terrorist attack in Kabul, Afghanistan that killed 13 U.S. service members, saying that there’s no room for politics in the discussion of the tragedy.

value.title: Biden doesn't deny report of US handing over names of Americans to Taliban: 'There may have been'
value.excerpt: President Biden did not deny a report circulating Thursday that officials in his administration had provided names of Americans in Afghanistan to the Taliban in order to help usher them safely to the airport.

value.title: Obama ethics chief blasts Hunter Biden's art scheme as 'absolutely appalling'
value.excerpt: Former President Obama's ethics chief on Wednesday ripped the Biden White House for brokering a deal last month so that Hunter Biden, and the American public at large, would never know who was buying his paintings.

value.title: Biden ally claims Trump greater 'threat' to US than al Qaeda
value.excerpt: A Democratic insider and vocal ally of President Biden claimed last week that former President Trump and his “Trumpist” supporters are a bigger threat to the United States than the Taliban and al Qaeda fighters.

value.title: With Biden poll numbers plunging, Democrats worry Afghan exit may impact next year's elections
value.excerpt: The rushed U.S. evacuation in Afghanistan appears to be a key contributing factor in the plunge in President Biden's approval rating in new polls. Some Democrats are worried the political fallout could impair their prospects in the 2022 midterms.

value.title: Pence slams Biden’s troop withdrawal as ‘foreign policy humiliation’
value.excerpt: In an interview on The Brian Kilmeade Show, Pence recalled Biden’s decision to fully withdraw by Sept. 11, saying that decision set the “disaster in motion.”

value.title: Sasse urges Biden to tell Taliban 'we're getting our people out however long it takes': 'Damn the deadline'
value.excerpt: In a blistering statement, Sen. Ben Sasse said Biden should be calling the shots, not the Taliban, who said there would be "no extensions" of the deadline set for withdrawal.

value.title: Kamala Harris calls Biden's Afghanistan decision 'courageous' as others in White House blame Trump
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris gave credit to President Biden for deciding to end the war in Afghanistan, even though members of the administration – including Biden himself – have blamed former President Trump for agreeing to withdraw U.S. troops.

value.title: Biden to be briefed on intelligence community COVID origin review as early as Tuesday
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to receive a briefing on the origin of COVID-19 from the intelligence community as early as Tuesday.
